WHY SHOULD YOU BECOME A MORNING PERSON?

What do you do when your alarm clock rings?

# Vocabulary
1. Sluggishness (n) /ˈslʌɡɪʃnəs/: moving or ​operating more slowly than usual:
2. Doze (v) /dəʊz/:  to have a ​short ​sleep, ​especially during the ​day:
3. Morning person (n) /ˈmɔːnɪŋ ˈpɜːsn/:  ​someonce full of ​energy in the ​mornings
4. Incentive (n) /ɪnˈsentɪv/:  something that ​encourages a ​person to do something
5. Wind down (v) /wɪnd daʊn/
6. Groggy (adj) /ˈɡrɒɡi/: ​weak and ​unable to ​think ​clearly or ​walk ​correctly, usually because of ​tiredness or ​illness:

# idioms
An early bird: a person who gets up, arrives, etc. very early
Have an early/a late night: to go to bed earlier or later than usual
